Daily menu of an obese child: no breakfast and dinner sausages
More than a third of children between the ages of 9 and 13 have overweight problems, where overweight affects 9% of the school population and obesity 5%.
Obese children mostly come from families with an unhealthy lifestyle, according to current research.
It once again demonstrates the importance of the environment where one grows for a healthy development of the person, as well as the models that serve as a reference.
At the table, obese children eat, for example, sausages at least twice as often as children from families with normal weight.
For dinner, more than 19% of the obese had French fries for dinner the day before the analysis, which is linked to the &quot;Obesity is not a coincidence&quot; prevention program.
In the families of overweight children there is no habit of practicing sports, which is applicable to the majority of current families, where only 15% of the children responded that their parents find time for exercise at least once a week. physical exercise.
Survey carried out on 900 children
The survey was carried out at the end of last school year and almost 900 children in Basic Education from all over the Czech Republic participated in it.
It was already the second edition of the &quot;Obesity is not a coincidence&quot; program, which is supported by the General Health Insurance Company and Unilever.
So far, more than 12 thousand children from the 4th to the 8th grade have participated in the project.
An adequate diet and plenty of exercise as a family are determining factors, which significantly reduce the number of overweight and even obese children.
&quot;Only half of the children surveyed have answered that they have five meals a day according to the regime: breakfast, lunch, lunch, snack and dinner, which is one of the basic conditions for a healthy diet,&quot; says one of the results of the survey. .
Without breakfast but with sausage for dinner
Specialists warn that, in a healthy development, details are also important, which also count, such as having a fixed time for breakfast as a family.
In the Czech Republic, however, only 23% of school families eat breakfast at the same time.
In most families, each one eats breakfast alone.
But the worst thing was discovering that 10% of homes do not have breakfast at all.
Breakfast is, however, the basis of a correct daily diet.
The study shows that in families with obese children, unhealthy French fries are consumed much more frequently.
Almost all - regardless of weight - drink sweet soft drinks daily (70%).
As a general rule, more than 40% of the children surveyed do sports, however, among their parents this result is reduced to less than half, only 15%.
make your diet
The next phase of the study made it possible for the chosen kids (204 boys and 172 girls from 13 schools) to create their own diets from all the possible offers according to their tastes and opinions.
&quot;The food preferences of Czech children between the ages of 12 and 15, from the point of view of healthy eating, are far from ideal.&quot;
Among his favorite foods are pasta, meat and sweets
&quot;The popularity of sweet soft drinks is especially alarming,&quot; the final report of the study warns.
As a main meal, pasta takes the cake, followed closely by poultry.
Children practically always reject legumes and their taste for fish and vegetables is very low.
Change to healthy habits
At the same time, the study shows that children are willing to change their eating habits if they receive the right information.
&quot;In the control group of study participants, who filled out the questionnaire after finishing the prevention program &quot;Obesity is not a coincidence&quot;, there was in many cases a significant change in favor of the principles of healthy eating &quot;, it is pointed out in the results of the study.
It is striking, for example, what is related to sweet soft drinks, where many children would begin to prefer normal, ordinary water.
The children would also choose poultry and fish for the main meal more frequently in the questionnaire and would restrict the consumption of sweet food and flour derivatives.
The stylist must also be a good psychologist, say the professionals
In the introductory article, How Stylists Learn, I already complained a bit that the initial lessons were already pretty loaded.
I had no idea how that would go.
Lectures by three industry professionals, how to dress problematic characters, and also a seminar on how it works in show business.
And it will be worse.
The closer the final exams are, the more information and practical tasks await us.
And although the course takes place every Saturday and Sunday, there is no room for a pin.
We are once we have studied with the director, Alena, (in the course there is no man) on how to dress the woman who does not have a perfect symmetry.
And so is the vast majority.
Someone is short-necked, someone has a slim figure without proper curves, and someone is overweight.
The stylist must know how to optically soften broad shoulders, lengthen a neck or recreate the necessary curves
We&#39;ve been given some tricks on how to make the body of women like Jennifer Lopez stand out, with huge breasts and hips but a narrow waist, and at the same time not dress too defiantly.
If, for example, the difference between the waist and hips is so much that the skirt or pants do not fit, it is worth having at least one extra piece of fabric sewn to size.
You certainly won&#39;t regret it, because clothes that fit perfectly are priceless.
With a tailored skirt you will feel much better than with one that does not stop moving, getting up, dancing at the waist, etc.
The stylized body can afford to wear clothes with pleats, ornaments, embroidery or draping.
There are certainly many different types of information and bodies, so I am glad that I have the whole week to put all this information in order in my head.
And even so, I&#39;m afraid that with the assigned task, I already have more than enough.
Each participant in the course has been assigned two celebrities, who must design two costumes: one for the day and one for the night.
You have to take into account the current appearance, the fashion style that suits the person in question.
I have had to &quot;dress&quot; Miranda Kerr, perhaps you know her from the Victoria&#39;s Secret campaign.
I scream inside, for me it is much better than, for example, Britney Spears or Christina Aguilera, who will have put on about a hundred kilos lately (please, take into account the exaggeration), or the very young Selena Gomez.
We have to cut out the dresses from magazines or find them on the internet and print them, to later elaborate them graphically.
The moodboard, which is what the complete result is called, also expresses our personal style and our relationship with graphic design.
It is also important to think about the graphic part of the styling.
The stylist, therefore, not only dresses physically, but also deals with, for example, the product pages in magazines (on specific topics, such as trends, bags, coats, etc.).
The stylist and designer Mario Kameník told us about all this.
But all this is left for Sunday.
The stylist must have a global vision.
The three specialist guests enlivened Saturday&#39;s conference with information on all kinds of bodies.
The stylist Honza Pokorný, the fashion designer Jakub Polanka and the fashion photographer Ben Renč.
Jakub reminded us that fashion is an illusion and the stylist should know how to take advantage of this.
And a good stylist knows how to work with the same item of clothing in different ways.
Variability is, in this case, essential.
Thus, such a trench coat (or as they say in English, trench-coat) can be dressed in the classic style with jeans and a T-shirt, but it can also be used to dress the naked body with high-heeled shoes and photograph it as if it were really a dress.
Or just roll up the sleeves and turn up the collar to get a totally different image.
&quot;Play with it,&quot; he insisted.
What I value most is the following advice: &quot;To start working, you first need to know all the rules.&quot;
&quot;Then you can break them,&quot; Jakub said.
It is finally clear to me why we memorize all those formulas, what is combined with what, why, if it later turns out that in fashion magazines we find different results.
Not to mention the parades.
Thanks to photographer Ben, I know that a stylist has to have more types of clothes in stock than they intend to shoot.
Thus, for a fashion story that has ten pages (therefore, ten outfits), you must have at least fifteen prepared, ready to wear.
And besides that the photos, the clothes work in combination with other clothes, all of them different from those used in reality.
All this must be taken into account when designing the outfit.
Honza Pokorný assured us that image and style alone are, in many cases, half the success.
Just look at Madonna, who is not exactly an extraordinary singer, but her image and marketing have made her a world star.
In the Czech Republic, at the moment, there is not yet a clear tendency to use the services of stylists.
Even famous people also find it useless (my skills are enough for me, my physical appearance is not that important).
And when someone asks us for our services, we must take into account that it is very likely that they will indicate a size that is very different from their real one (smaller).
Then all you have to do is googling and find out if gossip magazines have already written about it, if a certain celebrity has gotten fat/lost, etc.
On Sunday, Honza and Mario insisted that it is not enough for a stylist to focus on fashion, but rather that they have to understand outfits.
During your work, above all you must communicate with the people you saw, so it is essential to be a good psychologist.
He knows how to value people, he does not neglect himself, he defends his opinions.
&quot;When a director hires you to classify her wardrobe and complete it with beautiful clothes, you can&#39;t take and throw away everything that was there and say: &quot;oh, what a horror&quot;&quot;.
&quot;Find at least a couple of things that you can ponder and recommend for someone to wear,&quot; says Mario.
He himself also showed us that everything must fit into the so-called &quot;placovka&quot;, that is, the labor exchange.
This is fixed around the waist and all the necessary tools are kept there.
They are scissors-like objects, such as scissors, lint removers, or safety pins. There is also nylon thread (which is useful to the stylist during the photo session of products such as bags or hats), special clips for attaching garments in front, if this is larger (pins and other types of attachments are not allowed, as they could damage the fabric), or a sewing kit.
In order not to stay in passive listening and put something into practice, we have learned to cover the sole of our shoes.
Even during photo sessions in the studio, on a flat surface, the sole could be damaged and even more so the exterior.
And we did nothing more than cover and cover.
We couldn&#39;t touch the shoes with the scissors so as not to accidentally damage them.
So you had to be very clever.
Mario has given me joy by praising my work without reservation.
The truth is that I am not very good at those skills.
This is only a small part of everything we have heard throughout the weekend, in the second part of the course.
I have already realized that dedicating myself to styling at a professional level is not a bed of roses, but I don&#39;t care exactly what people say.
In Need for Speed: The Run you compete across America.
Review
A trip, initially carefree, is complicated by a series of oversights inappropriate for a routine trip during the morning shift.
To a certain extent, expectations were met, but this is of no use if, in reality, nothing extraordinary was intended.
The new installment, to which The Run is added to the title, aroused great expectations even before its premiere.
It promised that it would give new air to the old Need for Speed racing saga and, as a result of what has been shown, it appears as a game that should not end up being just another action genre again.
We are also curious as to how the inserted scenes would look, where the main character gets out of the car and walks on his own feet.
As often happens in NFS series, the results do not vary much from what we expected.
There are races that can be considered acceptable, but in the total calculation points are lost due to absurd failures, which have been appearing in the series for years.
In reality, they cannot even be called errors, but rather the incomprehensible reluctance of programmers.
The adventure starts very well.
You are introduced to a story, whose main character, Jack, has some personal problems; to solve them, he is offered to take part in an illegal race across America.
You sit behind the wheel on the West Coast, in San Francisco, and your mission is to get to New York first.
The idea is to offer something interesting.
The route is divided into ten stages and then into more than fifty races.
From this it follows that each race takes place on a different route and the stages are located in different environments, which are quite diverse and interesting.
In this way, one does not even remotely have the feeling that the game always offers the same thing.
Some of the environments are even pleasing to the eye, although the technical level of the graphics is equivalent to that of previous installments in the series.
Therefore, it is nothing special.
But the walk through the desert, the autumn landscape or the high mountains covered with snow produce a very pleasant visual effect.
Also, careers branch out from time to time for an outlier element.
So, for example, in the desert you find yourself in a sandstorm that reduces visibility.
On the other hand, in the mountains you have to be careful so that an avalanche does not bury you.
According to that, each of the races is very well developed.
There are only a couple of models, but that&#39;s enough.
For a moment, you try to overtake a required number of rivals (normal in a classic race), then you try to gain time (timed classic duel) and then a duel against a single opponent awaits you.
In the midst of all this the police sometimes show up, which only makes things even more difficult.
The novelty are the landscapes outside the car.
Interactive animations are presented when Jack, in most cases, has to escape from someone and you have to help him, always pressing the right button at the right time.
Nothing complicated.
It is surprising, however, that there are far fewer landscapes in the game than you might expect (specifically, there are only three).
But the end result is positive, because this element is not annoying and, in the already mentioned context, it is one of the elements that make the game more interesting.
The driving model follows in the footsteps of the previous episodes.
That means that today it is no longer a big deal, but it cannot be said that it is bad.
If you are looking for a realistic simulation, you can already look elsewhere.
But for a race conceived with a lot of action, this style of driving is quite convenient, although we can find something better among the competing games.
So far, everything in order.
But problems arise after a certain time.
Unlike the correctness of driving models, the same is no longer true of collisions.
Games of this type cannot be expected to recreate complicated deformations and collisions, but in fact before hitting any object, you cannot predict how your car will react, so not everything is in order.
It is typical that, when overtaking very closely or driving the car in normal traffic, there are only slight scratches, but in other almost identical situations, your car ends up doing uncontrolled pirouettes.
Or even just completely destroyed.
Thanks to the reset system, there are no big problems, but it can put you in a bad mood.
The resets are programmed in such a way that when you have an accident or go off the track, the game returns you to the last rescue point on the track.
However, in each race there are only five available resets.
If you consume them all, you have to restart the race from the beginning.
So it is only a help in case something goes wrong, but it is not very reliable.
Sometimes, not even resetting helps, it only helps to learn the given stage by heart.
A great disadvantage of the game is that the same events are repeated in different places.
In some curves, for example, you have to enter in a specific way; otherwise they are impossible to take.
Other times you find &quot;civilian&quot; vehicles somewhere always with the same configuration, even if you are the first, fifth or arrive five minutes before or after.
This is especially infuriating in situations when you see that two cars that are going to meet in opposite directions, your opponent overtakes without problems, but when you arrive, you must turn or brake.
It doesn&#39;t matter when you arrive, because it&#39;s programmed because the &quot;surprise&quot; will always happen right under your nose.
Opponents also have one more advantage.
Throughout the game you will arrive at places where, regardless of the moment, the same adversary will always overtake you in the same place.
Also this happens at the end of the game, on a long bridge, which is even more shocking.
Your opponent must arrive before you, at any cost.
When it&#39;s in front of you, it makes it difficult for you to see the cars coming in front of you, so at first you can smash the car to mush.
The idea of creating a game with maximum doses of suspense and adrenaline can be understood, but the execution is so apparent that you will surely be disappointed right away.
And it&#39;s a shame, because even if the model of the trip is simple, the game is fun and action-packed, so that it is often not possible to follow exactly what is happening and where.
And it really doesn&#39;t matter, if the credit takes the idea with fifty exclusive tracks or the classification in the race so that there is no room for boredom, or anything else.
An unusual idea is the change of cars during the races.
You have to be attentive to the gasoline pumps on the side of the road, because right there you have to change your car, although in the vast majority of cases what you have will suffice.
The cars are divided into three categories.
Sports cars are suitable for urban areas, American muscle cars for straight highways and exotic supercars for technical driving, for example on curvy mountain roads.
In addition to the main narrative thread, a parallel challenge thread also appears, that is, there are races in specific places that you will know from the stories.
Here you will get not only medals, but also experience points for your profile, which is used for both challenges and stories.
Upon reaching the top level, the driver is presented with various possibilities, starting with the car and ending with funds for the profile.
At the same time, an online Autolog function is connected, which compares your results with those of other players and makes other community functions available.
One of the most difficult elements to understand is how the last race in the story is made.
With the car you get to the subway tunnel (pass), where you start running in the dark along the tracks (pass).
The speedometer shows you between 150 and 200 km/h (pass) and, suddenly, the metro convoy arrives from behind and takes you ahead without further ado.
In the newsroom we will surely have a discussion about this for several days, about whether during the programming of the game no one thought even a little or if the authors really take us for a bunch of idiots.
The technical part of the game is nothing extraordinary, but at least the general visual effects are in most cases pleasant, sometimes even superb.
Well, what a pity that, in the most tense moments, the image quality is reduced and, sometimes, in a serious way.
This affects above all accidents involving many participants, when the continuous image quality is no longer valid.
The audio is fine and the soundtrack is a matter of taste.
In order to be liked by most of the youth group, the soundtrack falls into the &quot;everyone from their father and mother&quot; category, but it can be assumed that no one would buy the game just for its music.
The final feeling of Need for Speed: The Run is therefore quite confusing.
If the game avoided absolutely silly bugs, we&#39;d have a hard time calling The Run the best NFS game of recent years.
It feels like the game isn&#39;t over.
Fun is guaranteed, but be prepared because the bugs will hit you in the eyes with the force of airport reflectors.
The choirs of the Carolina University will participate in the concert &quot;Estudiantes de Terciopelo&quot;.
The joint celebration of International Student Day and the anniversary of the Velvet Revolution as a musical experience will take place for the third time at the Festa Academica festival.
During it, twenty choirs from secondary and university centers will perform.
The festival revolves around two concerts on November 17.
&quot;Carolina University has a high participation in the festival.&quot;
Among the current choirs are the choir of the Faculty of Pedagogy and the Faculty of Humanities, the festival committee includes the rector Václav Hampl,&quot; said the head of the organization, Jakub Čaloun.
The highlight of the entire festival is free admission for all audiences to the concert of the secondary choirs, which will be held on March 17 at 2:00 p.m. in front of the National Technical Library in Dejvice.
The program features the participation of Czech jazz player Karel Růžička and his Celebration Jazz Mass.
In the evening, the concert &quot;Velvet Students&quot; will be held at the venues of the Municipal House in Vynohrady, in which university choirs, including the choir of Carolina University, will take part.
The Festa Academica aims not only to celebrate International Student Day with dignity and commemorate the 22nd anniversary of the Velvet Revolution, but also to present choral music at the highest level to the public and encourage collaborative creation among young people.
The main organizer is the Czech Choir Union in cooperation with the Jan Kepler High School.
All the events were supported by the Mayor of Prague, Bohuslav Svoboda, and the Chancellor of Charles University, Václav Hampl.
The Festival will take place between November 16 and 20 between Prague and Pardubice.
The calendar offers, in addition to the celebratory concerts, a whole series of musical events, impromptu student shows and morning concerts.
Those interested can find more information on the festival website www.festaacademica.cz
