According to the data provided by the PREP, the difference between first and second place in the gubernatorial election is barely 27 percent, even without counting the votes corresponding to 879 of the 6,074 total tally sheets.
The possibility of counting &quot;vote by vote&quot; is a reality in what refers to the electoral process this year in Michoacán, where according to the data provided by the Preliminary Electoral Results Program (PREP) the difference between first and second place of the gubernatorial election is barely 27 percent, even without counting the votes corresponding to 879 of the 6,074 total tally sheets.
