Interviewed about the possibility of &quot;vote by vote&quot;, María de los Ángeles Llanderal explained that thanks to the approval of the corresponding guidelines by the General Council of the IEM, it will be possible to carry out partial and total recounts of the vote by the local electoral body.
In this way, the partial recount of votes, of one or more electoral packages, may occur in the event that: the results of the minutes do not coincide; There is no scrutiny and counting record in the polling station file or it is not in the possession of the president of the polling station; or, when there are obvious errors or alterations in the minutes.
In addition, the total recount of the votes received in all the voting booths may be carried out when there is an indication that the difference between the presumed winner of the election in question and the one who has obtained second place in the voting is equal to or less than one percentage point; as long as at the beginning of the session there is the express request of the representative of the party and/or coalition that nominated the second of the indicated candidates.
The total recount of the vote may also be carried out if, at the end of the ordinary count, it is established that the difference between the presumably winning candidate and the one located in second place is equal to or less than one percentage point, as long as there is the express request of the representative of the political party whose candidate came in second place, in which case the electoral packages that have been partially recounted will be excluded.
It is worth mentioning that the Morelia election is in this situation, where according to the PREP the difference between first and second place is barely 0.16 percent, although without counting the votes of 129 of the 923 total tallies.
